Melsanthi (head priest) E.S. Sankaran Namboodiri opened the Ayyappa temple at Sabarimala at 6 a.m. on Thursday.The Melsanthi closed the temple after covering the Ayyappa idol with sacred ash (vibhuti) by 6.30 a.m., marking the culmination of the two-month long annual Mandalam-Makaravilakku festival.The Thiruvabharanam, brought from the Pandalam Palace, was taken back to Pandalam in a procession. The procession will reach the Sastha Temple at Perinad on Friday, after a nightâ€™s halt at Laha Sathram on Thursday. The Thiruvabharanam will be brought back to the Pandalam Palace by 4 a.m. on Sunday.